cs.AR, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.DC 

The paper discusses challenges in programmability and efficiency in harnessing complex and diverse architectures, and proposes the use of low-overhead cross-layer abstractions to address these challenges. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including cs.AR (Architecture), cs.PL (Programming Languages), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). However, given the focus on hardware-software interfaces and optimizations for performance, cs.AR and cs.PL are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant but to a lesser extent.
